CIX. ΟΝ ΤΗΕ DEMISE OF JOHN URQUHART,1 OF CRAIGSTON.

Grand-uncle of the famous and eccentric Sir Thomas Urquhart of Cromarty. Died in November, 1631. The Castle of Craigston in King-Edward, Aberdeenshire, remains a monu- ment of his taste and affluence. Plura in note on Spalding⁷s Trubles, I. 26 (Spalding Club edition); Collections, etc„ 481-2, and Bulloch's Jmncsone, p. 162.

ARGUMENT.

Urquhart is gone, happiest of his time, now full of years and of those riches which he turned into ministering servants. Ye posterity of his, inheritors of his lands and fame, learn by his example how to live: learn also how to die.
